# Project Codex: Front-End Developer Assessment (Next.js + API Integration)

## Objective
Build a pixel-accurate e-commerce web app from the provided Figma using Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, React Server Components, and Server Actions for all API interactions.

## Tech Stack (Required)
- Next.js 15+ (App Router)
- React Server Components
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Server Actions (mandatory for API calls)

## Hard Constraints (Do Not Violate)
- Do NOT use `pages/` directory.
- Do NOT use Redux, Zustand, or unnecessary state libraries.
- Do NOT use `fetch()` in client components.
- Do NOT use axios in client components.
- Do NOT call APIs directly from client components.
- Do NOT call any database directly.
- Use only the provided API endpoints.

## API Integration Rules
- All API communication must happen via Server Actions only.
- Keep API logic centralized in server-side action files (e.g. `src/actions/*`).
- Use typed request/response models.
- Handle API failures explicitly (network/server/invalid response).
- Return normalized data structures from actions.
- Use `revalidate` / cache controls intentionally and document rationale.

## Allowed Patterns
- Server Components by default.
- Client Components only when interaction requires browser APIs/hooks.
- `fetch` is allowed only in server actions.
- Next.js built-in caching and revalidation controls are allowed.

## Design Requirements (Figma Fidelity)
Figma:
https://www.figma.com/design/UAQ0gFBqYduDOatXQqBJIY/E-commerce-web-site?node-id=0-1&t=axIG6ScXeXkDDxdG-1

Implementation must closely match:
- Layout and section structure
- Colors and typography
- Spacing and sizing
- Buttons and states
- Responsive behavior (mobile/tablet/desktop)

Pixel-accurate implementation is expected.

## API Endpoints
- All products: `https://mm-assesment-server.vercel.app/api/v1/products`
- Categories: `https://mm-assesment-server.vercel.app/api/v1/products/categories`
- Products by category (example): `https://mm-assesment-server.vercel.app/api/v1/products/category/jewelry`
- Single product (example): `https://mm-assesment-server.vercel.app/api/v1/products/1`

## Architecture Guidelines
- Prefer small, reusable, typed components.
- Keep a clear folder structure, for example:
  - `src/app` (routes/layout/pages)
  - `src/components` (UI and feature components)
  - `src/actions` (server actions only)
  - `src/lib` (helpers, formatters, constants)
  - `src/types` (API/domain types)
- Keep business/data transformation logic out of UI components.
- Keep components presentational when possible.

## Validation & Error Handling
- Validate API data shape before rendering.
- Gracefully handle loading, empty, and error states.
- Show user-friendly fallback messages.
- Avoid crashing UI on malformed API responses.

## Code Quality Standards
- Strict TypeScript usage (avoid `any` unless justified).
- Keep functions/components focused and readable.
- Use descriptive naming and consistent file organization.
- No dead code, no duplicated logic, no unnecessary abstraction.
- Follow ESLint and formatting rules in the repo.

## Performance Expectations
- Use Server Components for data-heavy rendering.
- Minimize client-side JS.
- Optimize images and avoid unnecessary rerenders.
- Use Next.js caching/revalidation intentionally per route/data type.

## Definition of Done
A task is complete only if:
1. Feature/UI matches Figma section requirements.
2. API data flows through Server Actions only.
3. Responsive behavior is correct across breakpoints.
4. Types are accurate and error states handled.
5. Lint/build pass successfully.
6. Changes are maintainable and clearly structured.

## Deliverables Checklist
- GitHub repository link
- Live Vercel deployment link
- `README.md` including:
  - setup/run instructions
  - architecture explanation
  - assumptions made
- `.env.example` with all required env variable keys (no secrets)

## Agent Output Style
When making changes:
- Briefly explain what changed and why.
- List touched file paths.
- Mention validation done (lint/build/manual checks).
- Suggest logical next steps only when helpful.
